  94def _filter_state_variables_written(expressions: List["Expression"]):
  95    ret = []
  96    for expression in expressions:
  97        if isinstance(expression, Identifier):
  98            ret.append(expression)
  99        if isinstance(expression, UnaryOperation):
 100            ret.append(expression.expression)
 101        if isinstance(expression, MemberAccess):
 102            ret.append(expression.expression)
 103        if isinstance(expression, IndexAccess):
 104            ret.append(expression.expression_left)
 105    return ret

 232    @property
 233    def name(self) -> str:
 234        """
 235        str: function name
 236        """
 237        if self._name == "" and self._function_type == FunctionType.CONSTRUCTOR:
 238            return "constructor"
 239        if self._function_type == FunctionType.FALLBACK:
 240            return "fallback"
 241        if self._function_type == FunctionType.RECEIVE:
 242            return "receive"
 243        if self._function_type == FunctionType.CONSTRUCTOR_VARIABLES:
 244            return "slitherConstructorVariables"
 245        if self._function_type == FunctionType.CONSTRUCTOR_CONSTANT_VARIABLES:
 246            return "slitherConstructorConstantVariables"
 247        return self._name

 267    @property
 268    def full_name(self) -> str:
 269        """
 270        str: func_name(type1,type2)
 271        Return the function signature without the return values
 272        The difference between this function and solidity_function is that full_name does not translate the underlying
 273        type (ex: structure, contract to address, ...)
 274        """
 275        if self._full_name is None:
 276            name, parameters, _ = self.signature
 277            full_name = ".".join(self._internal_scope + [name]) + "(" + ",".join(parameters) + ")"
 278            self._full_name = full_name
 279        return self._full_name

 286        Return the function signature without the return values
 287        """
 288        return ""

 298    def can_reenter(self, callstack=None) -> bool:
 299        """
 300        Check if the function can re-enter
 301        Follow internal calls.
 302        Do not consider CREATE as potential re-enter, but check if the
 303        destination's constructor can contain a call (recurs. follow nested CREATE)
 304        For Solidity > 0.5, filter access to public variables and constant/pure/view
 305        For call to this. check if the destination can re-enter
 306        Do not consider Send/Transfer as there is not enough gas
 307        :param callstack: used internally to check for recursion
 308        :return bool:
 309        """
 310        from slither.slithir.operations import Call
 311
 312        if self._can_reenter is None:
 313            self._can_reenter = False
 314            for ir in self.all_slithir_operations():
 315                if isinstance(ir, Call) and ir.can_reenter(callstack):
 316                    self._can_reenter = True
 317                    return True
 318        return self._can_reenter
 319
 320    def can_send_eth(self) -> bool:
 321        """
 322        Check if the function or any internal (not external) functions called by it can send eth
 323        :return bool:
 324        """
 325        from slither.slithir.operations import Call
 326
 327        if self._can_send_eth is None:
 328            self._can_send_eth = False
 329            for ir in self.all_slithir_operations():
 330                if isinstance(ir, Call) and ir.can_send_eth():
 331                    self._can_send_eth = True
 332                    return True
 333        return self._can_send_eth

 562    @property
 563    def nodes_ordered_dominators(self) -> List["Node"]:
 564        # TODO: does not work properly; most likely due to modifier call
 565        # This will not work for modifier call that lead to multiple nodes
 566        # from slither.core.cfg.node import NodeType
 567        if self._nodes_ordered_dominators is None:
 568            self._nodes_ordered_dominators = []
 569            if self.entry_point:
 570                self._compute_nodes_ordered_dominators(self.entry_point)
 571
 572            for node in self.nodes:
 573                # if node.type == NodeType.OTHER_ENTRYPOINT:
 574                if not node in self._nodes_ordered_dominators:
 575                    self._compute_nodes_ordered_dominators(node)
 576
 577        return self._nodes_ordered_dominators
 578
 579    def _compute_nodes_ordered_dominators(self, node: "Node"):
 580        assert self._nodes_ordered_dominators is not None
 581        if node in self._nodes_ordered_dominators:
 582            return
 583        self._nodes_ordered_dominators.append(node)
 584        for dom in node.dominance_exploration_ordered:
 585            self._compute_nodes_ordered_dominators(dom)

 960
 961    @property
 962    def solidity_signature(self) -> str:
 963        """
 964        Return a signature following the Solidity Standard
 965        Contract and converted into address
 966
 967        It might still keep internal types (ex: structure name) for internal functions.
 968        The reason is that internal functions allows recursive structure definition, which
 969        can't be converted following the Solidity stand ard
 970
 971        :return: the solidity signature
 972        """
 973        if self._solidity_signature is None:
 974            parameters = [
 975                convert_type_for_solidity_signature_to_string(x.type) for x in self.parameters
 976            ]
 977            self._solidity_signature = self.name + "(" + ",".join(parameters) + ")"
 978        return self._solidity_signature
 979
 980    @property
 981    def signature(self) -> Tuple[str, List[str], List[str]]:
 982        """
 983        (str, list(str), list(str)): Function signature as
 984        (name, list parameters type, list return values type)
 985        """
 986        if self._signature is None:
 987            signature = (
 988                self.name,
 989                [str(x.type) for x in self.parameters],
 990                [str(x.type) for x in self.returns],
 991            )
 992            self._signature = signature
 993        return self._signature
 994
 995    @property
 996    def signature_str(self) -> str:
 997        """
 998        str: func_name(type1,type2) returns (type3)
 999        Return the function signature as a str (contains the return values)
1000        """
1001        if self._signature_str is None:
1002            name, parameters, returnVars = self.signature
1003            self._signature_str = (
1004                name + "(" + ",".join(parameters) + ") returns(" + ",".join(returnVars) + ")"
1005            )
1006        return self._signature_str

1037        return self._reachable_from_functions
1038
1039    @property
1040    def all_reachable_from_functions(self) -> Set["Function"]:
1041        """
1042        Give the recursive version of reachable_from_functions (all the functions that lead to call self in the CFG)
1043        """
1044        if self._all_reachable_from_functions is None:
1045            functions: Set["Function"] = set()
1046
1047            new_functions = self.reachable_from_functions
1048            # iterate until we have are finding new functions
1049            while new_functions and not new_functions.issubset(functions):
1050                functions = functions.union(new_functions)
1051                # Use a temporary set, because we iterate over new_functions
1052                new_functionss: Set["Function"] = set()
1053                for f in new_functions:
1054                    new_functionss = new_functionss.union(f.reachable_from_functions)
1055                new_functions = new_functionss - functions
1056
1057            self._all_reachable_from_functions = functions
1058        return self._all_reachable_from_functions
1059
1060    def add_reachable_from_node(self, n: "Node", ir: "Operation"):
1061        self._reachable_from_nodes.add(ReacheableNode(n, ir))
1062        self._reachable_from_functions.add(n.function)

1071    def _explore_functions(self, f_new_values: Callable[["Function"], List]):
1072        values = f_new_values(self)
1073        explored = [self]
1074        to_explore = [
1075            c for c in self.internal_calls if isinstance(c, Function) and c not in explored
1076        ]
1077        to_explore += [
1078            c for (_, c) in self.library_calls if isinstance(c, Function) and c not in explored
1079        ]
1080        to_explore += [m for m in self.modifiers if m not in explored]
1081
1082        while to_explore:
1083            f = to_explore[0]
1084            to_explore = to_explore[1:]
1085            if f in explored:
1086                continue
1087            explored.append(f)
1088
1089            values += f_new_values(f)
1090
1091            to_explore += [
1092                c
1093                for c in f.internal_calls
1094                if isinstance(c, Function) and c not in explored and c not in to_explore
1095            ]
1096            to_explore += [
1097                c
1098                for (_, c) in f.library_calls
1099                if isinstance(c, Function) and c not in explored and c not in to_explore
1100            ]
1101            to_explore += [m for m in f.modifiers if m not in explored and m not in to_explore]
1102
1103        return list(set(values))

1285    def apply_visitor(self, Visitor: Callable) -> List:
1286        """

1370    def slithir_cfg_to_dot_str(self, skip_expressions=False) -> str:
1371        """
1372        Export the CFG to a DOT format. The nodes includes the Solidity expressions and the IRs
1373        :return: the DOT content
1374        :rtype: str
1375        """
1376        from slither.core.cfg.node import NodeType
1377
1378        content = ""
1379        content += "digraph{\n"
1380        for node in self.nodes:
1381            label = f"Node Type: {str(node.type)} {node.node_id}\n"
1382            if node.expression and not skip_expressions:
1383                label += f"\nEXPRESSION:\n{node.expression}\n"
1384            if node.irs and not skip_expressions:
1385                label += "\nIRs:\n" + "\n".join([str(ir) for ir in node.irs])
1386            content += f'{node.node_id}[label="{label}"];\n'
1387            if node.type in [NodeType.IF, NodeType.IFLOOP]:
1388                true_node = node.son_true
1389                if true_node:
1390                    content += f'{node.node_id}->{true_node.node_id}[label="True"];\n'
1391                false_node = node.son_false
1392                if false_node:
1393                    content += f'{node.node_id}->{false_node.node_id}[label="False"];\n'
1394            else:
1395                for son in node.sons:
1396                    content += f"{node.node_id}->{son.node_id};\n"
1397
1398        content += "}\n"
1399        return content

1458    def is_protected(self) -> bool:
1459        """
1460            Determine if the function is protected using a check on msg.sender
1461
1462            Consider onlyOwner as a safe modifier.
1463            If the owner functionality is incorrectly implemented, this will lead to incorrectly
1464            classify the function as protected
1465
1466            Otherwise only detects if msg.sender is directly used in a condition
1467            For example, it wont work for:
1468                address a = msg.sender
1469                require(a == owner)
1470        Returns
1471            (bool)
1472        """
1473
1474        if self._is_protected is None:
1475            if self.is_constructor:
1476                self._is_protected = True
1477                return True
1478            if "onlyOwner" in [m.name for m in self.modifiers]:
1479                self._is_protected = True
1480                return True
1481            conditional_vars = self.all_conditional_solidity_variables_read(include_loop=False)
1482            args_vars = self.all_solidity_variables_used_as_args()
1483            self._is_protected = (
1484                SolidityVariableComposed("msg.sender") in conditional_vars + args_vars
1485            )
1486        return self._is_protected
1487
1488    @property
1489    def is_reentrant(self) -> bool:
1490        """
1491        Determine if the function can be re-entered
1492        """
1493        # TODO: compare with hash of known nonReentrant modifier instead of the name
1494        if "nonReentrant" in [m.name for m in self.modifiers]:
1495            return False
1496
1497        if self.visibility in ["public", "external"]:
1498            return True
1499
1500        # If it's an internal function, check if all its entry points have the nonReentrant modifier
1501        all_entry_points = [
1502            f for f in self.all_reachable_from_functions if f.visibility in ["public", "external"]
1503        ]
1504        if not all_entry_points:
1505            return True
1506        return not all(("nonReentrant" in [m.name for m in f.modifiers] for f in all_entry_points))

1635    def _get_last_ssa_variable_instances(
1636        self, target_state: bool, target_local: bool
1637    ) -> Dict[str, Set["SlithIRVariable"]]:
1638        # pylint: disable=too-many-locals,too-many-branches
1639        from slither.slithir.variables import ReferenceVariable
1640        from slither.slithir.operations import OperationWithLValue
1641        from slither.core.cfg.node import NodeType
1642
1643        if not self.is_implemented:
1644            return {}
1645
1646        if self._entry_point is None:
1647            return {}
1648        # node, values
1649        to_explore: List[Tuple["Node", Dict]] = [(self._entry_point, {})]
1650        # node -> values
1651        explored: Dict = {}
1652        # name -> instances
1653        ret: Dict = {}
1654
1655        while to_explore:
1656            node, values = to_explore[0]
1657            to_explore = to_explore[1::]
1658
1659            if node.type != NodeType.ENTRYPOINT:
1660                for ir_ssa in node.irs_ssa:
1661                    if isinstance(ir_ssa, OperationWithLValue):
1662                        lvalue = ir_ssa.lvalue
1663                        if isinstance(lvalue, ReferenceVariable):
1664                            lvalue = lvalue.points_to_origin
1665                        if isinstance(lvalue, StateVariable) and target_state:
1666                            values[lvalue.canonical_name] = {lvalue}
1667                        if isinstance(lvalue, LocalVariable) and target_local:
1668                            values[lvalue.canonical_name] = {lvalue}
1669
1670            # Check for fixpoint
1671            if node in explored:
1672                if values == explored[node]:
1673                    continue
1674                for k, instances in values.items():
1675                    if k not in explored[node]:
1676                        explored[node][k] = set()
1677                    explored[node][k] |= instances
1678                values = explored[node]
1679            else:
1680                explored[node] = values
1681
1682            # Return condition
1683            if node.will_return:
1684                for name, instances in values.items():
1685                    if name not in ret:
1686                        ret[name] = set()
1687                    ret[name] |= instances
1688
1689            for son in node.sons:
1690                to_explore.append((son, dict(values)))
1691
1692        return ret
1693
1694    def get_last_ssa_state_variables_instances(
1695        self,
1696    ) -> Dict[str, Set["SlithIRVariable"]]:
1697        return self._get_last_ssa_variable_instances(target_state=True, target_local=False)

1704    @staticmethod
1705    def _unchange_phi(ir: "Operation"):
1706        from slither.slithir.operations import Phi, PhiCallback
1707
1708        if not isinstance(ir, (Phi, PhiCallback)) or len(ir.rvalues) > 1:
1709            return False
1710        if not ir.rvalues:
1711            return True
1712        return ir.rvalues[0] == ir.lvalue
1713
1714    def fix_phi(self, last_state_variables_instances, initial_state_variables_instances):
1715        from slither.slithir.operations import InternalCall, PhiCallback
1716        from slither.slithir.variables import Constant, StateIRVariable
1717
1718        for node in self.nodes:
1719            for ir in node.irs_ssa:
1720                if node == self.entry_point:
1721                    if isinstance(ir.lvalue, StateIRVariable):
1722                        additional = [initial_state_variables_instances[ir.lvalue.canonical_name]]
1723                        additional += last_state_variables_instances[ir.lvalue.canonical_name]
1724                        ir.rvalues = list(set(additional + ir.rvalues))
1725                    # function parameter
1726                    else:
1727                        # find index of the parameter
1728                        idx = self.parameters.index(ir.lvalue.non_ssa_version)
1729                        # find non ssa version of that index
1730                        additional = [n.ir.arguments[idx] for n in self.reachable_from_nodes]
1731                        additional = unroll(additional)
1732                        additional = [a for a in additional if not isinstance(a, Constant)]
1733                        ir.rvalues = list(set(additional + ir.rvalues))
1734                if isinstance(ir, PhiCallback):
1735                    callee_ir = ir.callee_ir
1736                    if isinstance(callee_ir, InternalCall):
1737                        last_ssa = callee_ir.function.get_last_ssa_state_variables_instances()
1738                        if ir.lvalue.canonical_name in last_ssa:
1739                            ir.rvalues = list(last_ssa[ir.lvalue.canonical_name])
1740                        else:
1741                            ir.rvalues = [ir.lvalue]
1742                    else:
1743                        additional = last_state_variables_instances[ir.lvalue.canonical_name]
1744                        ir.rvalues = list(set(additional + ir.rvalues))
1745
1746            node.irs_ssa = [ir for ir in node.irs_ssa if not self._unchange_phi(ir)]
1747

 233    @property
 234    def name(self) -> str:
 235        """
 236        str: function name
 237        """
 238        if self._name == "" and self._function_type == FunctionType.CONSTRUCTOR:
 239            return "constructor"
 240        if self._function_type == FunctionType.FALLBACK:
 241            return "fallback"
 242        if self._function_type == FunctionType.RECEIVE:
 243            return "receive"
 244        if self._function_type == FunctionType.CONSTRUCTOR_VARIABLES:
 245            return "slitherConstructorVariables"
 246        if self._function_type == FunctionType.CONSTRUCTOR_CONSTANT_VARIABLES:
 247            return "slitherConstructorConstantVariables"
 248        return self._name
 249
 250    @name.setter
 251    def name(self, new_name: str):
 252        self._name = new_name

 254    @property

 256        """
 257        Return a list of name representing the scope of the function
 258        This is used to model nested functions declared in YUL
 259
 260        :return:
 261        """
 262        return self._internal_scope

 266        self._internal_scope = new_scope

 268    @property
 269    def full_name(self) -> str:
 270        """
 271        str: func_name(type1,type2)
 272        Return the function signature without the return values
 273        The difference between this function and solidity_function is that full_name does not translate the underlying
 274        type (ex: structure, contract to address, ...)
 275        """
 276        if self._full_name is None:
 277            name, parameters, _ = self.signature
 278            full_name = ".".join(self._internal_scope + [name]) + "(" + ",".join(parameters) + ")"
 279            self._full_name = full_name
 280        return self._full_name
 281
 282    @property

 284    def canonical_name(self) -> str:
 285        """
 286        str: contract.func_name(type1,type2)
 287        Return the function signature without the return values
 288        """
 289        return ""

 299    def can_reenter(self, callstack=None) -> bool:
 300        """
 301        Check if the function can re-enter
 302        Follow internal calls.
 303        Do not consider CREATE as potential re-enter, but check if the
 304        destination's constructor can contain a call (recurs. follow nested CREATE)
 305        For Solidity > 0.5, filter access to public variables and constant/pure/view
 306        For call to this. check if the destination can re-enter
 307        Do not consider Send/Transfer as there is not enough gas
 308        :param callstack: used internally to check for recursion
 309        :return bool:
 310        """
 311        from slither.slithir.operations import Call
 312
 313        if self._can_reenter is None:
 314            self._can_reenter = False
 315            for ir in self.all_slithir_operations():
 316                if isinstance(ir, Call) and ir.can_reenter(callstack):
 317                    self._can_reenter = True
 318                    return True
 319        return self._can_reenter
 320
 321    def can_send_eth(self) -> bool:
 322        """
 323        Check if the function or any internal (not external) functions called by it can send eth
 324        :return bool:
 325        """
 326        from slither.slithir.operations import Call
 327
 328        if self._can_send_eth is None:
 329            self._can_send_eth = False
 330            for ir in self.all_slithir_operations():
 331                if isinstance(ir, Call) and ir.can_send_eth():
 332                    self._can_send_eth = True
 333                    return True
 334        return self._can_send_eth
 335

 340
 341
 342        :return:
 343        """

 345        return self.compilation_unit.solc_version >= "0.8.0"

 563    @property
 564    def nodes_ordered_dominators(self) -> List["Node"]:
 565        # TODO: does not work properly; most likely due to modifier call
 566        # This will not work for modifier call that lead to multiple nodes
 567        # from slither.core.cfg.node import NodeType
 568        if self._nodes_ordered_dominators is None:
 569            self._nodes_ordered_dominators = []
 570            if self.entry_point:
 571                self._compute_nodes_ordered_dominators(self.entry_point)
 572
 573            for node in self.nodes:
 574                # if node.type == NodeType.OTHER_ENTRYPOINT:
 575                if not node in self._nodes_ordered_dominators:
 576                    self._compute_nodes_ordered_dominators(node)
 577
 578        return self._nodes_ordered_dominators
 579
 580    def _compute_nodes_ordered_dominators(self, node: "Node"):
 581        assert self._nodes_ordered_dominators is not None
 582        if node in self._nodes_ordered_dominators:
 583            return
 584        self._nodes_ordered_dominators.append(node)
 585        for dom in node.dominance_exploration_ordered:
 586            self._compute_nodes_ordered_dominators(dom)

 887        from slither.core.cfg.node import NodeType
 888        from slither.slithir.operations import Return
 889        from slither.slithir.variables import Constant
 890
 891        if self._return_values is None:
 892            return_values = []
 893            returns = [n for n in self.nodes if n.type == NodeType.RETURN]
 894            [  # pylint: disable=expression-not-assigned

 962    @property
 963    def solidity_signature(self) -> str:
 964        """
 965        Return a signature following the Solidity Standard
 966        Contract and converted into address
 967
 968        It might still keep internal types (ex: structure name) for internal functions.
 969        The reason is that internal functions allows recursive structure definition, which
 970        can't be converted following the Solidity stand ard
 971
 972        :return: the solidity signature
 973        """
 974        if self._solidity_signature is None:
 975            parameters = [
 976                convert_type_for_solidity_signature_to_string(x.type) for x in self.parameters
 977            ]
 978            self._solidity_signature = self.name + "(" + ",".join(parameters) + ")"
 979        return self._solidity_signature
 980
 981    @property
 982    def signature(self) -> Tuple[str, List[str], List[str]]:
 983        """
 984        (str, list(str), list(str)): Function signature as
 985        (name, list parameters type, list return values type)
 986        """
 987        if self._signature is None:
 988            signature = (
 989                self.name,
 990                [str(x.type) for x in self.parameters],
 991                [str(x.type) for x in self.returns],
 992            )
 993            self._signature = signature
 994        return self._signature
 995
 996    @property
 997    def signature_str(self) -> str:
 998        """
 999        str: func_name(type1,type2) returns (type3)
1000        Return the function signature as a str (contains the return values)
1001        """
1002        if self._signature_str is None:
1003            name, parameters, returnVars = self.signature
1004            self._signature_str = (
1005                name + "(" + ",".join(parameters) + ") returns(" + ",".join(returnVars) + ")"
1006            )
1007        return self._signature_str

1040    @property
1041    def all_reachable_from_functions(self) -> Set["Function"]:
1042        """
1043        Give the recursive version of reachable_from_functions (all the functions that lead to call self in the CFG)
1044        """
1045        if self._all_reachable_from_functions is None:
1046            functions: Set["Function"] = set()
1047
1048            new_functions = self.reachable_from_functions
1049            # iterate until we have are finding new functions
1050            while new_functions and not new_functions.issubset(functions):
1051                functions = functions.union(new_functions)
1052                # Use a temporary set, because we iterate over new_functions
1053                new_functionss: Set["Function"] = set()
1054                for f in new_functions:
1055                    new_functionss = new_functionss.union(f.reachable_from_functions)
1056                new_functions = new_functionss - functions
1057
1058            self._all_reachable_from_functions = functions
1059        return self._all_reachable_from_functions
1060

1062        self._reachable_from_nodes.add(ReacheableNode(n, ir))
1063        self._reachable_from_functions.add(n.function)

1072    def _explore_functions(self, f_new_values: Callable[["Function"], List]):
1073        values = f_new_values(self)
1074        explored = [self]
1075        to_explore = [
1076            c for c in self.internal_calls if isinstance(c, Function) and c not in explored
1077        ]
1078        to_explore += [
1079            c for (_, c) in self.library_calls if isinstance(c, Function) and c not in explored
1080        ]
1081        to_explore += [m for m in self.modifiers if m not in explored]
1082
1083        while to_explore:
1084            f = to_explore[0]
1085            to_explore = to_explore[1:]
1086            if f in explored:
1087                continue
1088            explored.append(f)
1089
1090            values += f_new_values(f)
1091
1092            to_explore += [
1093                c
1094                for c in f.internal_calls
1095                if isinstance(c, Function) and c not in explored and c not in to_explore
1096            ]
1097            to_explore += [
1098                c
1099                for (_, c) in f.library_calls
1100                if isinstance(c, Function) and c not in explored and c not in to_explore
1101            ]
1102            to_explore += [m for m in f.modifiers if m not in explored and m not in to_explore]
1103
1104        return list(set(values))

1323    def cfg_to_dot(self, filename: str):
1324        """
1325            Export the function to a dot file
1326        Args:
1327            filename (str)
1328        """
1329        with open(filename, "w", encoding="utf8") as f:
1330            f.write("digraph{\n")
1331            for node in self.nodes:
1332                f.write(f'{node.node_id}[label="{str(node)}"];\n')
1333                for son in node.sons:
1334                    f.write(f"{node.node_id}->{son.node_id};\n")
1335
1336            f.write("}\n")

1338    def dominator_tree_to_dot(self, filename: str):
1339        """
1340            Export the dominator tree of the function to a dot file
1341        Args:
1342            filename (str)
1343        """
1344
1345        def description(node):
1346            desc = f"{node}\n"
1347            desc += f"id: {node.node_id}"
1348            if node.dominance_frontier:
1349                desc += f"\ndominance frontier: {[n.node_id for n in node.dominance_frontier]}"
1350            return desc
1351
1352        with open(filename, "w", encoding="utf8") as f:
1353            f.write("digraph{\n")
1354            for node in self.nodes:
1355                f.write(f'{node.node_id}[label="{description(node)}"];\n')
1356                if node.immediate_dominator:
1357                    f.write(f"{node.immediate_dominator.node_id}->{node.node_id};\n")
1358
1359            f.write("}\n")

1361    def slithir_cfg_to_dot(self, filename: str):
1362        """
1363        Export the CFG to a DOT file. The nodes includes the Solidity expressions and the IRs
1364        :param filename:
1365        :return:
1366        """

1368        with open(filename, "w", encoding="utf8") as f:
1369            f.write(content)

1371    def slithir_cfg_to_dot_str(self, skip_expressions=False) -> str:
1372        """
1373        Export the CFG to a DOT format. The nodes includes the Solidity expressions and the IRs
1374        :return: the DOT content
1375        :rtype: str
1376        """
1377        from slither.core.cfg.node import NodeType
1378
1379        content = ""
1380        content += "digraph{\n"
1381        for node in self.nodes:
1382            label = f"Node Type: {str(node.type)} {node.node_id}\n"
1383            if node.expression and not skip_expressions:
1384                label += f"\nEXPRESSION:\n{node.expression}\n"
1385            if node.irs and not skip_expressions:
1386                label += "\nIRs:\n" + "\n".join([str(ir) for ir in node.irs])
1387            content += f'{node.node_id}[label="{label}"];\n'
1388            if node.type in [NodeType.IF, NodeType.IFLOOP]:
1389                true_node = node.son_true
1390                if true_node:
1391                    content += f'{node.node_id}->{true_node.node_id}[label="True"];\n'
1392                false_node = node.son_false
1393                if false_node:
1394                    content += f'{node.node_id}->{false_node.node_id}[label="False"];\n'
1395            else:
1396                for son in node.sons:
1397                    content += f"{node.node_id}->{son.node_id};\n"
1398
1399        content += "}\n"
1400        return content

1459    def is_protected(self) -> bool:
1460        """
1461            Determine if the function is protected using a check on msg.sender
1462
1463            Consider onlyOwner as a safe modifier.
1464            If the owner functionality is incorrectly implemented, this will lead to incorrectly
1465            classify the function as protected
1466
1467            Otherwise only detects if msg.sender is directly used in a condition
1468            For example, it wont work for:
1469                address a = msg.sender
1470                require(a == owner)
1471        Returns
1472            (bool)
1473        """
1474
1475        if self._is_protected is None:
1476            if self.is_constructor:
1477                self._is_protected = True
1478                return True
1479            if "onlyOwner" in [m.name for m in self.modifiers]:
1480                self._is_protected = True
1481                return True
1482            conditional_vars = self.all_conditional_solidity_variables_read(include_loop=False)
1483            args_vars = self.all_solidity_variables_used_as_args()
1484            self._is_protected = (
1485                SolidityVariableComposed("msg.sender") in conditional_vars + args_vars
1486            )
1487        return self._is_protected

1489    @property
1490    def is_reentrant(self) -> bool:
1491        """
1492        Determine if the function can be re-entered
1493        """
1494        # TODO: compare with hash of known nonReentrant modifier instead of the name
1495        if "nonReentrant" in [m.name for m in self.modifiers]:
1496            return False
1497
1498        if self.visibility in ["public", "external"]:
1499            return True
1500
1501        # If it's an internal function, check if all its entry points have the nonReentrant modifier
1502        all_entry_points = [
1503            f for f in self.all_reachable_from_functions if f.visibility in ["public", "external"]
1504        ]
1505        if not all_entry_points:
1506            return True
1507        return not all(("nonReentrant" in [m.name for m in f.modifiers] for f in all_entry_points))
1508

1636    def _get_last_ssa_variable_instances(
1637        self, target_state: bool, target_local: bool
1638    ) -> Dict[str, Set["SlithIRVariable"]]:
1639        # pylint: disable=too-many-locals,too-many-branches
1640        from slither.slithir.variables import ReferenceVariable
1641        from slither.slithir.operations import OperationWithLValue
1642        from slither.core.cfg.node import NodeType
1643
1644        if not self.is_implemented:
1645            return {}
1646
1647        if self._entry_point is None:
1648            return {}
1649        # node, values
1650        to_explore: List[Tuple["Node", Dict]] = [(self._entry_point, {})]
1651        # node -> values
1652        explored: Dict = {}
1653        # name -> instances
1654        ret: Dict = {}
1655
1656        while to_explore:
1657            node, values = to_explore[0]
1658            to_explore = to_explore[1::]
1659
1660            if node.type != NodeType.ENTRYPOINT:
1661                for ir_ssa in node.irs_ssa:
1662                    if isinstance(ir_ssa, OperationWithLValue):
1663                        lvalue = ir_ssa.lvalue
1664                        if isinstance(lvalue, ReferenceVariable):
1665                            lvalue = lvalue.points_to_origin
1666                        if isinstance(lvalue, StateVariable) and target_state:
1667                            values[lvalue.canonical_name] = {lvalue}
1668                        if isinstance(lvalue, LocalVariable) and target_local:
1669                            values[lvalue.canonical_name] = {lvalue}
1670
1671            # Check for fixpoint
1672            if node in explored:
1673                if values == explored[node]:
1674                    continue
1675                for k, instances in values.items():
1676                    if k not in explored[node]:
1677                        explored[node][k] = set()
1678                    explored[node][k] |= instances
1679                values = explored[node]
1680            else:
1681                explored[node] = values
1682
1683            # Return condition
1684            if node.will_return:
1685                for name, instances in values.items():
1686                    if name not in ret:
1687                        ret[name] = set()
1688                    ret[name] |= instances
1689
1690            for son in node.sons:
1691                to_explore.append((son, dict(values)))
1692
1693        return ret
1694

1696        self,
1697    ) -> Dict[str, Set["SlithIRVariable"]]:

1705    @staticmethod
1706    def _unchange_phi(ir: "Operation"):
1707        from slither.slithir.operations import Phi, PhiCallback
1708
1709        if not isinstance(ir, (Phi, PhiCallback)) or len(ir.rvalues) > 1:
1710            return False
1711        if not ir.rvalues:
1712            return True
1713        return ir.rvalues[0] == ir.lvalue
1714
1715    def fix_phi(self, last_state_variables_instances, initial_state_variables_instances):
1716        from slither.slithir.operations import InternalCall, PhiCallback
1717        from slither.slithir.variables import Constant, StateIRVariable
1718
1719        for node in self.nodes:
1720            for ir in node.irs_ssa:
1721                if node == self.entry_point:
1722                    if isinstance(ir.lvalue, StateIRVariable):
1723                        additional = [initial_state_variables_instances[ir.lvalue.canonical_name]]
1724                        additional += last_state_variables_instances[ir.lvalue.canonical_name]
1725                        ir.rvalues = list(set(additional + ir.rvalues))
1726                    # function parameter
1727                    else:
1728                        # find index of the parameter
1729                        idx = self.parameters.index(ir.lvalue.non_ssa_version)
1730                        # find non ssa version of that index
1731                        additional = [n.ir.arguments[idx] for n in self.reachable_from_nodes]
1732                        additional = unroll(additional)
1733                        additional = [a for a in additional if not isinstance(a, Constant)]
1734                        ir.rvalues = list(set(additional + ir.rvalues))
1735                if isinstance(ir, PhiCallback):
1736                    callee_ir = ir.callee_ir
1737                    if isinstance(callee_ir, InternalCall):
1738                        last_ssa = callee_ir.function.get_last_ssa_state_variables_instances()
1739                        if ir.lvalue.canonical_name in last_ssa:
1740                            ir.rvalues = list(last_ssa[ir.lvalue.canonical_name])
1741                        else:
1742                            ir.rvalues = [ir.lvalue]
1743                    else:
1744                        additional = last_state_variables_instances[ir.lvalue.canonical_name]
1745                        ir.rvalues = list(set(additional + ir.rvalues))
1746
1747            node.irs_ssa = [ir for ir in node.irs_ssa if not self._unchange_phi(ir)]
1748

def can_reenter(self, callstack=None) -> bool: 
299    def can_reenter(self, callstack=None) -> bool:
300        """
301        Check if the function can re-enter
302        Follow internal calls.
303        Do not consider CREATE as potential re-enter, but check if the
304        destination's constructor can contain a call (recurs. follow nested CREATE)
305        For Solidity > 0.5, filter access to public variables and constant/pure/view
306        For call to this. check if the destination can re-enter
307        Do not consider Send/Transfer as there is not enough gas
308        :param callstack: used internally to check for recursion
309        :return bool:
310        """
311        from slither.slithir.operations import Call
312
313        if self._can_reenter is None:
314            self._can_reenter = False
315            for ir in self.all_slithir_operations():
316                if isinstance(ir, Call) and ir.can_reenter(callstack):
317                    self._can_reenter = True
318                    return True
319        return self._can_reenter

def slithir_cfg_to_dot_str(self, skip_expressions=False) -> str: 
1371    def slithir_cfg_to_dot_str(self, skip_expressions=False) -> str:
1372        """
1373        Export the CFG to a DOT format. The nodes includes the Solidity expressions and the IRs
1374        :return: the DOT content
1375        :rtype: str
1376        """
1377        from slither.core.cfg.node import NodeType
1378
1379        content = ""
1380        content += "digraph{\n"
1381        for node in self.nodes:
1382            label = f"Node Type: {str(node.type)} {node.node_id}\n"
1383            if node.expression and not skip_expressions:
1384                label += f"\nEXPRESSION:\n{node.expression}\n"
1385            if node.irs and not skip_expressions:
1386                label += "\nIRs:\n" + "\n".join([str(ir) for ir in node.irs])
1387            content += f'{node.node_id}[label="{label}"];\n'
1388            if node.type in [NodeType.IF, NodeType.IFLOOP]:
1389                true_node = node.son_true
1390                if true_node:
1391                    content += f'{node.node_id}->{true_node.node_id}[label="True"];\n'
1392                false_node = node.son_false
1393                if false_node:
1394                    content += f'{node.node_id}->{false_node.node_id}[label="False"];\n'
1395            else:
1396                for son in node.sons:
1397                    content += f"{node.node_id}->{son.node_id};\n"
1398
1399        content += "}\n"
1400        return content

def is_protected(self) -> bool: 
1459    def is_protected(self) -> bool:
1460        """
1461            Determine if the function is protected using a check on msg.sender
1462
1463            Consider onlyOwner as a safe modifier.
1464            If the owner functionality is incorrectly implemented, this will lead to incorrectly
1465            classify the function as protected
1466
1467            Otherwise only detects if msg.sender is directly used in a condition
1468            For example, it wont work for:
1469                address a = msg.sender
1470                require(a == owner)
1471        Returns
1472            (bool)
1473        """
1474
1475        if self._is_protected is None:
1476            if self.is_constructor:
1477                self._is_protected = True
1478                return True
1479            if "onlyOwner" in [m.name for m in self.modifiers]:
1480                self._is_protected = True
1481                return True
1482            conditional_vars = self.all_conditional_solidity_variables_read(include_loop=False)
1483            args_vars = self.all_solidity_variables_used_as_args()
1484            self._is_protected = (
1485                SolidityVariableComposed("msg.sender") in conditional_vars + args_vars
1486            )
1487        return self._is_protected

1716        from slither.slithir.operations import InternalCall, PhiCallback

1743                    else:
